        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 5 at 7:58PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>At 758 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Averill Park, or near Nassau, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Totem Lodge, East Schodack, Garfield, East Poestenkill, North
Stephentown, West Stephentown, Averill Park, Hoag Corners, Millers
Corners, Taborton, Sand Lake, Center Berlin, Glass Lake, Denault
Corners, Shivers Corners, Best, Stephentown, Dunham Hollow,
Wyomanock, and Cherryplain.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
